e/or_else ceremony\\\" body=\\\"The metadata setters use `take().or_else(...)` to mean 'keep the first value seen', temporarily moving each `Option` out and restoring it. Straight `if self.field.is_none() { self.field = ... }` assignments preserve the exact first-value-wins behavior while deleting ownership noise that makes the parser look more abstract than it is.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs\\\" start=61 end=98 priority=3 confidence=0.78}\\n\\nI filtered out a few tempting deletions because they are part of the POC contract, not just scaffolding: the separate `seen-record-hashes` vs transcript-list dedupe, the source provenance scalars, the hashed `session-id` scalar, and the redaction count/boolean fields are all reflected in the agent-session docs.\\n\\nValidation run while reviewing: `cargo test -p but-agentlog` passed, and `cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps` was clean.\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:22:30.840Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}